Building an API Backend

If you are doing hashtag#softwaredevelopment the only thing that has value is code running in production.

If you are doing hashtag#datascience the only thing that has value is code that produces useful insight.

Sometimes these two worlds meet. More now than ever hashtag#artificialintelligence and hashtag#machinelearning 
models need to be integrated into products. This is typically done, in practice, through a hashtag#microservice / API.
Here are some resources to get you started building them yourself.

Carnegie Mellon University course by Christian Kastner website (17.445) -> https://lnkd.in/e_SrYDb

Deploy an ML model ( hashtag#python scikit-learn ) as a REST API -> https://lnkd.in/esyH863

Deploy a Keras model ( hashtag#python keras ) -> https://lnkd.in/eSyvcg6

Deploy a Keras model repo -> https://lnkd.in/ev9iAzP

Deploy an R model using Docker -> https://lnkd.in/eSEAwYk

Deploy a tensorflow model on Android -> https://lnkd.in/eDG8ejM

